cc:Work.dc:title: Anything For A Laugh's map of Undermountain

g.title: These stairs raise into the ceiling until the lever is pulled.

path.title: Cube Farm full of gelatenous cubes.

g.title: This section of floor turns into stairs when the lever is pulled.

rect.title: This room is filled with acidic mud that will drown people in armor and damage people who aren't.

This room is divided into black and white squares, checkerboard style. The black squares can turn into solid darkness when they are stepped on. Either the black or white squares (depending on the position of the lever) will zap lightning throughtout the room.

path.title: This appears to be the Cube Farm incubator.

rect.title: This scaffold reaches up high enough for someone to paint on the 40' ceiling.
This was marked on the Smoke Powder smugglers' map. Dunno what it is yet.
These rungs go up to a 3' diamater tube that had a sack of loot in it.
Ziggurat of horrible flaming spiky death and snakes.
Secret door with lock. We used a Knock spell on it.
Secret door with unknown mechanism. Henkles opened it the hard way.
This bridge is a trap. If you attempt to cross it, it turns into a pair of slides, dumping you into the mud below. It can also be used to teleport to Nesme
This lever causes the stairs to appear.
This statue turns into a snake. Although it's obviously valuable, it does not like to leave the room.
Cache for the smoke powder. Dug by Brogan as an enlarged Umber Hulk, hidden by Stone Shape.

circle.title: Magical gate, we think. Probably how the smoke powder has been coming in.

rect.title: Illusionary wall. Hard to disbelieve, but easy to walk through.
We have not made any attempt to get past this portcullis.
This lever controls which set of tiles sets off the lightning. Moving it to either end also triggers lightning. Put it straight up to disable the trap.
This trapdoor opens onto a 2'x2' shaft with rungs on one side. It's a long way down, and we dropped a light button into it. There's water at the bottom.

g.title: "We never go that way, don't know why."
Food and nasty bats in here.
Fi'i'tharg Lair. Frog thing? Ogres leave it tribute.
"We never go this way because it would make us dead."
Good area to hunt giant lizards.
Bigass spiders here, at least two, maybe five. White fuzzy cold kind.

rect.title: This room has a looted couch and other debris in it.
This pit has a nasty robot lobster in it.
This 10' deep pit had a gelatenous cube in it.
Don't fall into this pit again.
We don't remember the solution to this puzzle.
Not solving this puzzle will set off the flaming dragons. We think, anyway.

path.title: These walkways are slightly slippery and curved to make falling easy.

rect.title: This is the balcony where Dethen was hanging.

circle.title: This is a spiral staircase, going down a long ways IIRC.

path.title: To avoid getting hit by a trap, you need to pass through the gap in this fence.
To avoid getting hit by a trap, you need to jump/climb over this fence.
Jump over this step to avoid the trap.

rect.title: This button raises the floor so one can get at the secret doors, but can't leave through the north exit.
The North corridor floor is 10' above the E/W corridor floor.
This is a ladder to room above
This is a cage on chains that hangs from the ceiling. It is lowered/raised by rotating the statue in the room above.
We don't remember the details of this trapped door.
Big creature that demanded food to let us past.

circle.title: I think this is a fountain that you walk through to trigger the staircase.
This is a round thing in the Litch's labratory.

rect.title: This is a rectangular thing in the litch's labratory.
This is a rectangular thing in the litch's labratory.
This is an archway/tunnel under the walkway.
This is a tunnel/archway under the walkway.
This is a tunnel/archway under the walkway.
This is a tunnel/archway under the walkway.
This compartment held a chest guarded by a little pict.
This floor is covered with sand, but don't mistake it for a sandbox.
Wand of Wonder statue, with hidden room under it.
Row of dots on the map. Portcullis?
Picture of an animal face on the map.
This picture of a face has holes for the occupants of the secret room to observe and fire on people on the stairs.
circular pools of water, one on the floor, one on the ceiling
Rectangle on the map, no clue why.
Picture of a door painted on the wall.
This was someone's hidout, with hammocks, tin plates, cups, etc

This room has a balcony, and webs containing sacks of loot. They are protected by metal spiders who only allow each party to take one bag, and not by using magic. They can also turn the room into a null-magic zone. The floor is covere with nasty poisoned spikes.

path.title: Ogres, bugbears, and a beast cooking over a big fire.

rect.title: This pit contains enhanced gravity, and a teleportal that teleports ones remains back to the top.
This floor is covered with sand, but don't mistake it for a sandbox.

path.title: Magic is unusable in this room.

rect.title: The orc that was trapped here used this area as a sandbox.
Drinkable water that does not require going near the (dead) giant gar.

path.title: This water-filled room had a giant gar in it.

g.title: Teleportal to a2: "If you're reading this, it's already too late"
Teleportal from a1: The "too late" teleportal dumps you here.

rect.title: This room is filled with boiling oil. *and* magic only works above the pillars.
This pit has a nasty robot lobster in it.
This pit is deep and has 25' of water in it.

circle.title: This pit has enhanced gravity in it, for extra pain.

rect.title: This chair made out of bones used to have arms that turned into poison-spitting snakes and it was covered in gems.
This privy contains a hidden lever to open the nearby secret door.

path.title: This is a one-way secret door.

rect.title: Something about touching the red tiles opens this door.
This bas-relief image of a face contains arrow slits so that people in the secret room can fire on the staircase.
illusionary wall that hides a watchpost

circle.title: Big fire pit with a big beast being cooked over it

path.title: This is the skeleton of a dragon's tail, a well known landmark in Undermountain.

rect.title: This lever opens the secret door to cooking room
If you pump this hidden lever, the Dexter Dance path appears.
Touching this mirror when the lightning bolts trigger teleports you to Myth Drannor.
This statue glows enough to almost illuminate the water-filled room.
This giant altar to Lolth has been much abused by Stewart in the past.
We have never found out the purpose of this slipcovered couch.
This gate asks you a riddle, and if you answer it, it opens, allowing you to bypass the null-magic room.
Turning this statue raises and lowers the cage on chains in the room below.
This opens into an alley in Waterdeep. The watch has told us to never be caught near it again.
All mistakes in jumping between columns result in one being teleported here. It sinks under weight. After a minute or so it teleports you back to the entrance.
This trapdoor opens onto a ladder that leads to the room below.
This statue has two sheathes that you can insert a sword or dagger into, and an outstretched hand. When you put a sword in the sheath and put a serpentine in the hand, the sword becomes enchanted

path.title: This portcullis falls down when someone steps on the pressure plate.

rect.title: This is a reverse-gravity trap, with nasty spikes on the ceiling.

circle.title: This statue shoots lightning bolts. There's a secret door in its base that leads to a spiral staircase.

rect.title: This portcullis blocks the path when the pressure plate is stepped on.
This wall slid down a while after we were teleported to the flooded room with the giant gar in it.
We looted this exploded chest surrounded by undead on Uktar 12 1369.
This pressure plate drops portcullises ahead and behind and dumps hundreds of pounds of garbage on the person who triggered it.
This statue acts as a Wand of Wonder, blasting the room randomly.

circle.title: This pool has a mirror image on the ceiling, and may or may not be home to a Water Weird.

text.tspan: Somewhere around here is a secret library in a place
where the corridor goes around a 30x30 area.

rect.title: This was filled in with a dark color on the map we acquired.
This had an X in it on the map we acquired.
This line was on the map we acquired. We don't know what it means.

circle.title: We don't know what this circle represents.
We don't know what this circle represents.
